Question

Consider the \(L\)-system defined below:

  • Start: A.A
  • Rules:
    A > BC
    B > B[+C][-C]
    C > CAD
    D > DD[+D+D][-D-D]
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 5
  • Angle
    • 60

When we use the resulting string to drive turtle graphics, using https://draemm.li/various/fractals/l-systems/, what image is produced?

(You might need to adjust other parameters to get image rotated, centered, and scaled.)

Answerlist

  • A
  • B
  • C
  • D
  • E
  • F
  • G
  • H

Solution

The correct pattern is pattern H.

  1. Use the link: https://draemm.li/various/fractals/l-systems/
  2. Copy in the starting string, replacement rules, number of recursions, and angle.
  3. Adjust the center and scale to clearly see the pattern. You might also need to rotate the pattern.
  4. Select the correct pattern.

In case youre interested in the parameters of the other patterns shown:

Pattern A

  • Start: [+A][-B]
  • Rules:
    A > [-CA-CB]A
    B > [+CB+CA]B
    C > CC
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 6
  • Angle
    • 90

Pattern B

  • Start: A
  • Rules:
    A > -B+B+B+B+B+B
    B > BB[-CCA]
    C > CC
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 5
  • Angle
    • 60

Pattern C

  • Start: A
  • Rules:
    A > B++B++B++B++B
    B > B[-CCC-CC-CCA][----CC-CCB]B
    C > CC
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 5
  • Angle
    • 36

Pattern D

  • Start: AA
  • Rules:
    A > B-AA-B
    B > AB+B+AB
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 5
  • Angle
    • 90

Pattern E

  • Start: [A]+++[A]+++[A]
  • Rules:
    A > A[---XB][-XB][+XB][+++XB]
    B > XB[++XA][--XA]XA
    X > XX
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 4
  • Angle
    • 40

Pattern F

  • Start: A++A++A++A
  • Rules:
    A > B-ABA-B
    B > A+BB+A
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 4
  • Angle
    • 135

Pattern G

  • Start: A------A
  • Rules:
    A > [---B][-B][+B][+++B]
    B > BD[++DA][--DA]B
    D > DD
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
    • 5
  • Angle
    • 30

Pattern H

  • Start: A.A
  • Rules:
    A > BC
    B > B[+C][-C]
    C > CAD
    D > DD[+D+D][-D-D]
  • Number of recursions (number of iterations):
